cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing social media content streams (specifically Twitter) to identify users who can help combat Zika epidemics. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper describes the prototype architecture for their approach. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with noisy and sparse signal in social media data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper mentions training a classifier to select topic-relevant tweets. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also relevant as the paper discusses the potential for using social media analysis to complement traditional disease prevention programs led by health authorities.
